	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />OK, I have a basic 6502 CPU up and running and am now starting work on the PPU. My problem is: what does its memory contain after loading the ROM? I know what's supposed to be in there, but where in the ROM am I supposed to find it?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Disch</b> [ Wed Nov 21, 2007 9:18 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Super Mario Bros has 32K PRG (2 banks) and 8K CHR (1 bank).  If your ROM does not indicate it has CHR-ROM, your header is either bad, or your ROM is bad, or you're reading the header wrong.
<br />
<br />In any event... typically when games do not have any CHR-ROM, you give them 8K CHR-RAM at ppu$0000-1FFF

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


